signatures.name: wrote_proc_memory
signatures.short_description: Wrote to the memory of another process
signatures.description: A process wrote data to an area of memory in another process.

signatures.name: executes_dropped_exe
signatures.description: A process was created using a dropped executable.

signatures.name: susevent_adjustprivilegetoken
signatures.description: A privilege for an access token was adjusted. Windows uses the token to control the ability of the user to perform various system-related operations.

signatures.name: files_antiav_general
signatures.short_description: Attempts to identify installed anti-virus software via file checks
signatures.description: Enumeates the file system and looks for the presence of files and libraries known to be part of various anti-virus solutions. Identifying the installed security software is generally related to evasion techniques.

signatures.name: registry_writes_large_value
signatures.short_description: Writes a long series of bytes to a registry key
signatures.description: Creates or modifies a registry key with a large amount of byte data, possibly to store a binary or configuration.
